Package ca.ualberta.cs.scandaloutraveltracker

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    UserInformationDialog.UserInformationDialogListener
    Uses an interface so that any class that wishes to use the UserInformationDialog should also implement what happens on the positive and negative clicks of the alert dialog.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClaimApplication
    Helps setup the application for when the app is launched.
    ClaimListAdapter
    The ClaimListAdapter allows essential information from a Claim to be displayed in a ListView.
    ConnectivityChangeReceiver
    The ConnectivityChangeReceiver helps the application determine if there is or is not a connection to the Internet.
    Constants
    Class contains all the values that are constant throughout the application.
    DatePickerFragment
    Creates a DatePicker dialog.
    DestinationListAdapter
    Allows essential information from the Destination class to be displayed in a ListView.
    DialogCreator
    The DialogCreator class helps to create dialogs throughout the application.
    ExpenseListAdapter
    An adapter that allows an expense to display its essential information in a ListView.
    StateSpinner
    The StateSpinner extends the Spinner class and just adds the functionality of being able to check if the spinner has been opened or if it has not been opened.
    SyncQueueItem
    The SyncQueueItem class is a helper class for syncing the claim data to the online elastic search servers.
    TagParser
    TagParser returns a list of starting and ending indices of tags prefixed with a # and post-fixed with a space.
    UserInformationDialog
    The UserInformationDialog is a dialog that has all the relevant information pertaining to a user that is to be shown before a user logs in to the actual application.
    UserListAdapter
    The UserListAdapter is used when you wish to create a ListView's child view that shows appropriate user information to the user using the app.
